reviews.review_text: Classic Dead Acoustic show, great setlist and awesome banter between songs (Godzilla conversation after Dark Hollow)

Great show but archival I think the other Nov. 8 taping is at least marginally better than this offering. Yes, this is a killer show and it's great to have a record of the days when the Dead put on an acoustic set followed by a NRPS set followed by their own sets, but, also yes, be aware that this is a distorted, mono mix. Archival more than musical.
It's All over Now Baby Blue Headlines the show, followed with sickest version ever of going down the road - Phenominal
Get the new 2005 version of this show There is a new stereo version of this show, here at Archive.org at: New version. which is restored from the original master tapes. Go get that one !
